City authorities say that despite water restrictions, Cape Town residents are still using too much water. CAPE TOWN - City of Cape Town officials have renewed calls for residents to reduce water consumption following a decline in dam levels.Municipal dam levels are currently at 45.4%.Authorities say that despite water restrictions, Capetonians are still using too much water.The city's Peter Flower says the aim is for residents to keep water consumption at winter levels . We have a very high peak of demand in summer. If we could try to get everybody to stay within their winter consumption, meaning your essential needs for water, we d be able to meet a decent level coming out of this summer. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)